# Generate sample data

plt.ylabel('Y-axis Label')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
from sklearn.datasets import load_iris
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load Iris dataset
data = load_iris()
X = data.data

# Apply PCA
pca = PCA(n_components=2)
X_pca = pca.fit_transform(X)

# Plot PCA-transformed data
plt.scatter(X_pca[:, 0], X_pca[:, 1], c=data.target, cmap='viridis', alpha=0.8)
plt.title('PCA on Iris Dataset')
plt.xlabel('Principal Component 1')
plt.ylabel('Principal Component 2')
plt.show()

from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

# Sample data
x = np.random.rand(50)
y = np.random.rand(50)
z = np.random.rand(50)

# 3D Scatter Plot
fig = plt.figure()
ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')
ax.scatter(x, y, z, c=z, cmap='viridis', marker='o')
ax.set_title('3D Scatter Plot')
ax.set_xlabel('X-axis')
ax.set_ylabel('Y-axis')
ax.set_zlabel('Z-axis')
plt.show()

import folium

# Create a map
m = folium.Map(location=[20.5937, 78.9629], zoom_start=5)  # Centered on India

# Add airport markers
airports = [
    {"name": "Delhi Airport", "location": [28.5562, 77.1000]},
    {"name": "Mumbai Airport", "location": [19.0896, 72.8656]},
]
for airport in airports:
    folium.Marker(airport["location"], popup=airport["name"]).add_to(m)

# Save map
m.save("airports_map.html")

from wordcloud import WordCloud
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Sample text
text = "data visualization word cloud python data analysis scatter plot"

# Generate word cloud
wordcloud = WordCloud(background_color="white", width=800, height=400).generate(text)

# Display word cloud
plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
plt.axis("off")
plt.show()
